                    "OldMan3",
                    "Just t'the north a here is this mighty woodland. S'called the spirit forest.{w}{br}Once upon a time, I lived there too, in this li'l hamlet deep within.{w}{br}Th' village is home to the last kin o' the dark one of old, Loptyr.{w}{br}They say it all started with Saint Maira,{w}{br}exiled by the empire for darin' to sympathize with mortal men.{w}{br}In my day, there was this gorgeous girl livin' there called Cigyun:{w}{br}the last heir o' Loptyr's bloodline, she was.{w}{br}She lived 'er life under close guard,{w}{br}the villagers wary o' lettin' the blood o' Loptyr loose into the world.{w}{br}Alas, Cigyun grew weary o' the tedious forest life an' she left it all behind,{w}{br}breakin' ancient commandments.{w}{br}A couple o' years later, she came back, 'cept now she was pregnant.{w}{br}Never said who the father was, mind.{w}{br}Before long Cigyun died, even as she gave birth t' her daughter.{w}{br}From what I 'eard, the hamlet's old prophet took 'er in and raised the girl as 'er own.{w}{br}If the little girl's still alive, she'd 'ave to be 'bout seventeen or eighteen by now...{w}",
